<paragraph blockId="1.[151,540,1624,1646]" box="[151,540,1624,1646]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">
= 
<taxonomicName authority="Mamaev, 1990" authorityName="Mamaev" authorityYear="1990" box="[171,441,1624,1646]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Ubinomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[171,284,1624,1646]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Ubinomyia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mamaev, B. M." box="[290,441,1624,1646]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" pagination="12 - 28" refId="ref13802" refString="Mamaev, B. M. (1990) Description of new genera and species and key to genera of Palaearctic gall midges of the subfamily Porricondylinae (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Acta Zoologica Bulgarica, 40, 12 - 28. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1990">Mamaev, 1990</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[447,540,1624,1645]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">syn. nov.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1690,2003]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,1152]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="247" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">
<bibRefCitation author="Mamaev, B. M. &amp; Soyunov, O. S." box="[151,512,1690,1715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" pagination="65 - 67" refId="ref13896" refString="Mamaev, B. M. &amp; Soyunov, O. S. (1989) Description of a new genus of non-gallmaking gall midges, Desertepidosis Mam. et Sojun. gen. n., from Turkmenistan (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Izvestiyea Akademii Nauk Turkmenskoi SSR, Seriya Biologichesikh Nauk, 1989 (4), 65 - 67. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1989">Mamaev and Soyunov (1989)</bibRefCitation>
introduced this genus for two species from 
<collectingCountry box="[1078,1236,1690,1715]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mamaev, 1966" authorityName="Mamaev" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Stackelbergiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phryganophila">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Stackelbergiella phryganophila</emphasis>
Mamaev, 1966
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mamaev &amp; Soyunov, 1989" authorityName="Mamaev &amp; Soyunov" authorityYear="1989" box="[555,1135,1726,1751]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Desertepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis box="[555,811,1726,1751]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Desertepidosis pallida</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mamaev, B. M. &amp; Soyunov, O. S." box="[821,1135,1727,1751]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" pagination="65 - 67" refId="ref13896" refString="Mamaev, B. M. &amp; Soyunov, O. S. (1989) Description of a new genus of non-gallmaking gall midges, Desertepidosis Mam. et Sojun. gen. n., from Turkmenistan (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Izvestiyea Akademii Nauk Turkmenskoi SSR, Seriya Biologichesikh Nauk, 1989 (4), 65 - 67. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1989">Mamaev &amp; Soyunov, 1989</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, assuming it was a faunal element of arid environments. Our finding in 
<collectingCountry box="[658,747,1762,1787]" name="Sweden" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Sweden</collectingCountry>
of a third species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Jaschhof, 2013" authorityName="Jaschhof" authorityYear="2013" box="[956,1257,1762,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Desertepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borealis">
<emphasis box="[956,1079,1762,1787]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">D. borealis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C." box="[1087,1257,1762,1787]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" pagination="1 - 392" refId="ref13524" refString="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C. (2013) The Porricondylinae (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae) of Sweden, with notes on extralimital species. Studia dipterologica Supplement, 20, 1 - 392." type="journal article" year="2013">Jaschhof, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, challenged this assumption. A recent taxonomic revision (
<bibRefCitation author="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C." box="[640,1030,1798,1823]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" pagination="1 - 392" refId="ref13524" refString="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C. (2013) The Porricondylinae (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae) of Sweden, with notes on extralimital species. Studia dipterologica Supplement, 20, 1 - 392." type="journal article" year="2013">Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof 2013: 111ff.</bibRefCitation>
) revealed the dicerurine affinity of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mamaev &amp; Soyunov" authorityYear="1989" box="[151,317,1834,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Desertepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,317,1834,1859]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Desertepidosis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its resemblance to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mamaev" authorityYear="1990" box="[581,706,1834,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Ubinomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[581,706,1834,1859]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Ubinomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mamaev" authorityYear="1990" box="[760,899,1834,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Arctepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[760,899,1834,1859]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Arctepidosis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, two genera established by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mamaev, B. M." box="[1211,1394,1835,1859]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" pagination="12 - 28" refId="ref13802" refString="Mamaev, B. M. (1990) Description of new genera and species and key to genera of Palaearctic gall midges of the subfamily Porricondylinae (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Acta Zoologica Bulgarica, 40, 12 - 28. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1990">Mamaev (1990)</bibRefCitation>
. As regards 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mamaev" authorityYear="1990" box="[242,381,1870,1895]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Arctepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[242,381,1870,1895]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Arctepidosis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a recent examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[715,763,1872,1896]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mamaev, 1990" authorityName="Mamaev" authorityYear="1990" box="[869,1200,1870,1895]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Arctepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jamalensis">
<emphasis box="[869,1021,1870,1895]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">A. jamalensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mamaev, B. M." box="[1030,1200,1871,1895]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" pagination="12 - 28" refId="ref13802" refString="Mamaev, B. M. (1990) Description of new genera and species and key to genera of Palaearctic gall midges of the subfamily Porricondylinae (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Acta Zoologica Bulgarica, 40, 12 - 28. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1990">Mamaev, 1990</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, made clear that this genus is justifiably regarded as distinct from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mamaev &amp; Soyunov" authorityYear="1989" box="[676,843,1906,1931]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Desertepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[676,843,1906,1931]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Desertepidosis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C." box="[860,1256,1906,1931]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" pagination="546 - 570" refId="ref13622" refString="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C. (2017) Mycophagous gall midges (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae: Lestremiinae, Micromyinae, Winnertziinae, Porricondylinae): first records in Sweden and descriptions of closely related new species from elsewhere. Zootaxa, 4226 (4), 546 - 570. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4226.4.6" type="journal article" year="2017">Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof 2017: 558ff.</bibRefCitation>
). In the present study we revisited the generic justification of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mamaev" authorityYear="1990" box="[665,789,1942,1967]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Ubinomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[665,789,1942,1967]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Ubinomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with the result that this genus is no longer maintained as separate from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mamaev &amp; Soyunov" authorityYear="1989" box="[316,482,1978,2003]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Desertepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[316,482,1978,2003]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Desertepidosis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mamaev, B. M." box="[498,680,1979,2003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" pagination="12 - 28" refId="ref13802" refString="Mamaev, B. M. (1990) Description of new genera and species and key to genera of Palaearctic gall midges of the subfamily Porricondylinae (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Acta Zoologica Bulgarica, 40, 12 - 28. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1990">Mamaev (1990)</bibRefCitation>
did not highlight characters distinguishing 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mamaev" authorityYear="1990" box="[1181,1306,1978,2003]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Ubinomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1181,1306,1978,2003]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Ubinomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other porricondyline genera, but we found that a peculiarity in the male genitalia—the gonocoxal apodemes merged into a joint structure—was the only relevant distinction to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof 2013: 111)" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityPageNumber="111" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" baseAuthorityPageNumber="111" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[760,1308,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Desertepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[760,926,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Desertepidosis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C." box="[941,1299,188,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" pagination="1 - 392" refId="ref13524" refString="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C. (2013) The Porricondylinae (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae) of Sweden, with notes on extralimital species. Studia dipterologica Supplement, 20, 1 - 392." type="journal article" year="2013">Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof 2013: 111</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. As will be shown here, exactly the same structure is present in 
<taxonomicName authority="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof, 2019" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2019" box="[736,931,225,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Desertepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grytsjoenensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[736,931,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">D. grytsjoenensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[938,1028,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[938,1028,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, a species resembling 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jaschhof" authorityYear="2013" box="[1282,1407,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Desertepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borealis">
<emphasis box="[1282,1407,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">D. borealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to such an extent that we did not differentiate between the two of them in our 2013 revision. With the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName authority="Mamaev, 1990" authorityName="Mamaev" authorityYear="1990" box="[151,566,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Ubinomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cardinalis">
<emphasis box="[151,395,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Ubinomyia cardinalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mamaev, B. M." box="[401,566,296,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" pagination="12 - 28" refId="ref13802" refString="Mamaev, B. M. (1990) Description of new genera and species and key to genera of Palaearctic gall midges of the subfamily Porricondylinae (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Acta Zoologica Bulgarica, 40, 12 - 28. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1990">Mamaev, 1990</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(the only species ever assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mamaev" authorityYear="1990" box="[952,1076,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Ubinomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[952,1076,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Ubinomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and two new species described here, there are now six species classified with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[666,832,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Desertepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[666,832,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Desertepidosis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the basis for studying the taxonomy of this genus is everything but good: larvae remain unknown; the female of only one of the species (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mamaev" authorityYear="1990" box="[1248,1397,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Ubinomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cardinalis">
<emphasis box="[1248,1397,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">D. cardinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is described; and even males are rarely collected. As a result, three of the species have never been encountered outside their 
<typeStatus box="[302,350,440,464]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">type</typeStatus>
localities; only two are represented in collections by more than three specimens; and only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jaschhof" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Desertepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borealis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">D. borealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been found in more than one country. Why 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[780,946,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Desertepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[780,946,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Desertepidosis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are so rare is unclear, but interesting in this context is that three different species were found co-occurring in the same place in 
<collectingCountry box="[1073,1165,511,536]" name="Sweden" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Sweden</collectingCountry>
. All but one of 
<specimenCount box="[1337,1436,511,536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" type="male">23 males</specimenCount>
studied here were obtained by Malaise trapping. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mamaev &amp; Soyunov" authorityYear="1989" box="[705,959,548,573]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Desertepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis box="[705,959,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Desertepidosis pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the only species with toothed gonostylus and markedly tapered tegmen (MJ, personal observation in 2012), might be misclassified in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[1195,1361,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Desertepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1195,1361,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Desertepidosis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is retained in this genus only because a better, alternative placement is not available. New morphological information gathered here is used for updating the generic diagnosis (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C." box="[861,1167,655,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" pagination="1 - 392" refId="ref13524" refString="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C. (2013) The Porricondylinae (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae) of Sweden, with notes on extralimital species. Studia dipterologica Supplement, 20, 1 - 392." type="journal article" year="2013">Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof 2013</bibRefCitation>
: 112). Finally, a key to males is presented in order to facilitate the recognition of unnamed species, which are likely to be found in regions not yet surveyed for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[382,548,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Desertepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[382,548,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Desertepidosis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="247" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1152]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,764,789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
As pointed out earlier (
<bibRefCitation author="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C." box="[602,971,764,789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" pagination="1 - 392" refId="ref13524" refString="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C. (2013) The Porricondylinae (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae) of Sweden, with notes on extralimital species. Studia dipterologica Supplement, 20, 1 - 392." type="journal article" year="2013">Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof 2013: 112</bibRefCitation>
), male morphology of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[1240,1406,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Desertepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1240,1406,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Desertepidosis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is decidedly regressive, with symptoms of degeneration found in the compound eyes (see the reduced eye bridge), antennae (several species with fewer than 14 flagellomeres), palpi (several species with only 3 short segments), and wings (narrow outline, vein M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[506,514,886,900]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">4</subScript>
vestigial or absent). The costal break, which is conspicuously wide, lies either before or behind the apex of the wing, and the claws are either untoothed or equipped with a large basal tooth, which both are variations seldom met in porricondylines supposed to be so closely related. Characteristic of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[151,317,982,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Desertepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,317,982,1007]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Desertepidosis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the structure of the male genitalia, notably the gonostyli, which are large, subcylindrical, and toothless; the gonocoxae, whose large ventral emargination is U-shaped; the narrow, elongate tegmen, which lacks any fine structures; and the long, slender ejaculatory apodeme, whose base is strongly broadened in some of the species (as in many 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spungis" authorityYear="1987" box="[392,539,1090,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Neurepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[392,539,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Neurepidosis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see below). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mamaev &amp; Soyunov" authorityYear="1989" box="[700,956,1090,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Desertepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis box="[700,956,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Desertepidosis pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species deviating from this pattern, is unlikely to be correctly classified in this genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
